{
  "doc_id": "11664",
  "text": "In conclusion, the solution (21), with a Hubble rate as in [CITATION_1] , is stable, for small χ values, so during inlfation. Note however that the solution (21) is one particular solution of the system of equations (19) and (26) . In general, there might exist alternative solutions to this dynamical system, but the fact that the solution (21) is stable makes this solution an attractor of the dynamical system. Therefore, any class of solutions of (19) and (26), will asymptotically coincide with (21) .",
